com.ibm.xmi.framework
Class FactoryAdapter

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.ibm.xmi.framework.FactoryAdapter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Factory
public class FactoryAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Factory

The framework uses this class by default when loading XMI files to create XMI objects and values using the implementation classes for the data hierarchy. You may subclass from this class to create your own implementation classes for the data hierarchy interfaces, or to create your own subclasses of the implementation classes for the data hierarchy.

A subclass of this class is automatically created for you when you generate code using UML2Java.

If you subclass this class, you need to register an instance of your subclass with the framework by using the FactoryRegister class.

It is probably easier to subclass this class rather than implement the Factory interface directly yourself, especially if you only need to override a few of the methods, like the makeXMIObject ones, for example.
